        "kind": "pull_request",
        "title": "feat: add AWS Lambda MicroVM provider",
        "body": "## Summary\n\n- add the direct, delegated `aws-lambda-microvm` provider using AWS's new Lambda MicroVM SDK\n- add the bundled ARM64 runner image, archive sync, streamed execution, retained reuse, pause/resume, cleanup, and strict endpoint/token handling\n- add provider/unit/runner tests, guarded live-smoke coverage, generated provider metadata, changelog, and setup/operations docs\n\nAWS references:\n\n- https://aws.amazon.com/about-aws/whats-new/2026/06/aws-lambda-microvms/\n- https://docs.aws.amazon.com/lambda/latest/dg/lambda-microvms-guide.html\n\n## Verification\n\n- `go vet ./...`\n- `go test -race ./...`\n- `node --test scripts/*.test.js`\n- Worker format, lint, typecheck, 652 tests, and dry-run builds\n- `scripts/check-docs.sh`\n- ARM64 runner Docker build plus container health/streamed-exec E2E\n- autoreview: clean after fixing image-rotation claim routing and ARM64 target validation\n\nThe real AWS live smoke was attempted but stopped before provisioning because no Lambda MicroVM runner image ARN is configured in this environment. The guarded script reports that prerequisite as `environment_blocked`; it can be run with `CRABBOX_AWS_LAMBDA_MICROVM_IMAGE` after the runner image is built in AWS.\n",
